name: scenery of you
description:
"in the scenery of the spring there is nothing superior, nothing inferior. flowering branches grow naturally, some short, some long" 
within this simple phrase lies nature's innate defiance of perfectionism. as an artist (and other dysfunctions), beating the occasional round of perfectionism is a mountain climb in itself.  if you are not secure in who you are and what you want, it will spiral, it will destroy, it will become one of the roots of a self-doubting parasite if you let it. 
to fully accept and combat this, is to be truly free within, and alongside our wilderness.  
keep creating
